75. Write a Java program to test if the first and the last element of an array of integers are same. (Condition 1)
The length of the array must be greater than or equal to 2. (Condition 2)
>KeyTakeAway: Must state all condition provided

//<OWN METHOD>
import java.lang.*;
public class w3 {
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        int[] array = {50, -20, 0, 30, 40, 60, 10};
        System.out.println(array[0] == array[array.length-1]);
    }
}

>>
false


// <SAMPLE SOLUTION>
import java.lang.*;
 public class Exercise75 {
 public static void main(String[] args)
 {
    int[] num_array = {50, -20, 0, 30, 40, 60, 10};
    
	System.out.println (num_array.length >= 2 && num_array[0] ==  num_array[num_array.length-1]);
 }
}
